Use Playwright's built-in locator auto-waiting combined with `waitForSelector` and a fallback handler. Here's a robust pattern:

```ts
import { test, expect } from '@playwright/test';

test('closes toast notification if present', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto('https://agency.example.org/dashboard');

  // Try to click 'Close' if the toast appears
  const closeLocator = page.getByLabel('Close notification');
  await closeLocator.click({ timeout: 3000 }).catch(() => {
    // No-op: toast was not shown
  });

  // Proceed with main test flow
  await expect(page.getByRole('main')).toBeVisible();
});
```

Alternatively, for more control (e.g., multiple toasts), use `addLocatorHandler`:

```ts
await page.addLocatorHandler(
  page.getByLabel('Close notification'),
  async () => {
    // Handler auto-clicks once
    return; // Playwright will auto-click the locator if handler returns nothing
  },
  { times: 1 }
);

await page.goto('https://agency.example.org/dashboard');
// Handler triggers automatically when toast appears
await page.getByRole('button', { name: 'Submit' }).click();
```

✅ Best practices:
- Prefer `aria-label` over `text()` for close buttons (SC 4.1.2: Name, Role, Value)
- Use `getByLabel` — more robust than `getByText`
- Avoid `click({ force: true })` — it bypasses accessibility checks

Create `playwright.config.ts` in your project root:

```ts
import { defineConfig, devices } from '@playwright/test';

export default defineConfig({
  testDir: './tests',
  fullyParallel: true,
  forbidOnly: !!process.env.CI,
  retries: process.env.CI ? 2 : 0,
  workers: 1,
  reporter: 'html',
  use: {
    // Base URL to use in actions like `await page.goto('/')`
    baseURL: 'https://agency.example.org',

    // Trace on failure
    trace: 'on-first-retry',

    // Collect trace when retrying the failed test
    traceVideo: 'on-first-retry',

    // Timeouts
    actionTimeout: 15_000, // e.g., 15 seconds
    expect: {
